WEBVTT

00:00:08.375 --> 00:00:10.043
my name is Charlie Harvey and

00:00:10.043 --> 00:00:14.014
I work here at Port Elgin School
as a cultural support worker.

00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:15.815
Indigenous cultural support worker.

00:00:15.815 --> 00:00:18.985
My given name, my spirit name
that was given to me through a naming

00:00:18.985 --> 00:00:23.456
ceremony is actually Derek Cebu Psalm one,
which means gentle river waters.

00:00:24.290 --> 00:00:27.560
And I'm here today
to talk about indigenous education

00:00:27.560 --> 00:00:31.197
and how it, is reflected
in the students identities in our school.

00:00:31.664 --> 00:00:35.502
Okay, well, indigenous, culture is,

00:00:35.635 --> 00:00:38.505
represented in this school
in different ways.

00:00:38.505 --> 00:00:41.641
When you come in the building,
we have bulletin boards, and sometimes we

00:00:41.641 --> 00:00:46.379
have mock teepees, or I'll put up displays
for certain, events that are happening

00:00:46.379 --> 00:00:51.151
within the indigenous culture, like,
September 30th as every child matters.

00:00:51.184 --> 00:00:54.287
We just had MMW yesterday or no Monday.

00:00:54.821 --> 00:00:59.159
And, in other ways, we,
we do things within the school.

00:00:59.159 --> 00:01:01.361
So I might go into classrooms

00:01:01.361 --> 00:01:04.397
and do some medicine will teachings
or other teachings about the culture.

00:01:04.964 --> 00:01:08.535
I'll take students one on one
or in small groups and then we learn

00:01:09.135 --> 00:01:12.238
anything from language
to medicine, more teachings.

00:01:12.238 --> 00:01:15.208
We have, the seven sacred teachings.

00:01:16.676 --> 00:01:18.044
We do one every month

00:01:18.044 --> 00:01:21.047
so that the entire school learns
about our teachings.

00:01:21.081 --> 00:01:24.551
We do drum circles at lunchtime.

00:01:24.551 --> 00:01:28.655
We also perform in the assemblies
and the concerts that they have.

00:01:29.489 --> 00:01:34.594
We have we actually have, minimal
learning space outside that we can go to.

00:01:34.594 --> 00:01:38.731
And there's a structure out there where
we're hoping to get a TV on, on premise,

00:01:39.265 --> 00:01:41.901
to use as an outdoor classroom.

00:01:41.901 --> 00:01:45.939
And we can go out and we can do smudging
and we can do different, outdoor

00:01:45.939 --> 00:01:46.406
teachings.

00:01:46.406 --> 00:01:49.742
Outdoor learning is really, really big
within the indigenous community

00:01:49.742 --> 00:01:50.243
and culture.

00:01:50.243 --> 00:01:54.614
So, there's a PBL going on right now.

00:01:55.115 --> 00:01:58.017
That's,
that's focusing on indigenous culture,

00:01:58.017 --> 00:02:00.220
talking about wampum belts
or learning about wampum

00:02:00.220 --> 00:02:03.723
belts, the creation story
and other things like that.

00:02:03.723 --> 00:02:07.961
So we're kind of like implementing a lot
of different teachings within the PBL.

00:02:08.561 --> 00:02:11.664
And I take those
those students out to smudge as well.

00:02:11.664 --> 00:02:15.468
So, I work alongside the teachers,
the faculty, the staff,

00:02:15.568 --> 00:02:16.302
anything they need.

00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:19.772
If if anybody wants question answers,
I can go into the classroom and help

00:02:20.206 --> 00:02:24.477
teach about the culture that way
just to, you know, maybe take away

00:02:24.477 --> 00:02:28.481
some misgivings that the students
might think about our culture.

00:02:28.948 --> 00:02:31.951
So, yeah, there's a lot of different

00:02:32.152 --> 00:02:35.421
facets that that we can
include culture in the school.

00:02:35.421 --> 00:02:37.957
And this school is really inclusive
when it comes to that.

